    <string name="transport_legacy_hint">Use this for older TVs without Wireless debugging.</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_1_title">Step 1 — Enable debugging</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_1_body">On the TV, enable Developer options and USB, network, or ADB debugging.</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_2_title">Step 2 — Find the TV\'s IP address</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_2_body">Look in the TV\'s Network settings. The ADB port is usually 5555.</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_3_title">Step 3 — Connect and accept the prompt</string>
    <string name="transport_legacy_step_3_body">Enter both values and connect, then accept the debugging prompt on the TV (choose Always allow if available).</string>
